title._content: [Portrait of Bunk Johnson, George Lewis, Alcide Pavageau, Kaiser Marshall, Jim Robinson, and Don Ewell, Stuyvesant Casino, New York, N.Y., ca. June 1946] (LOC)

description._content: Gottlieb, William P., 1917-, photographer. [Portrait of Bunk Johnson, George Lewis, Alcide Pavageau, Kaiser Marshall, Jim Robinson, and Don Ewell, Stuyvesant Casino, New York, N.Y., ca. June 1946] 1 negative : b&w ; 3 1/4 x 4 1/4 in. Caption from Down Beat: Below, the New Orleans band now playing at the Stuyvesant Casino. Notes: Gottlieb Collection Assignment No. 207 Reference print available in Music Division, Library of Congress. Purchase William P. Gottlieb Forms part of: William P. Gottlieb Collection (Library of Congress). In: The Record Changer, v. 5, no. 4 (June 46, 1946), p. 19. Subjects: Ewell, Don Johnson, Bunk, 1879-1949 Lewis, George, 1900-1968 Marshall, Kaiser Pavageau, Alcide, 1888-1969 Robinson, Jim, 1892-1976 Big bands--1940-1950. Jazz musicians--1940-1950. Trumpet players--1940-1950. Stuyvesant Casino Format: Film negatives--1940-1950. Group portraits--1940-1950. Portrait photographs--1940-1950.
